The Rumelys and the Zimmermans were devout Roman Catholics, and the family faith determined the course of Edward's education. He attended a parochial school in La Porte and St. Joseph's Academy in Rensselaer, Indiana; spent eight months under the tutelage of Father Schweitzer, his mother's cousin, at Sinsinnawa Mound, Wisconsin;
